, n.d.). The fallacy seems to have an explanation in a strong\~}{\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\cf17\loch
loss}{\loch\cf17\loch
\~}{\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\cf17\loch
aversion}{\loch\cf17\loch
\~in humans (Tversky & Kahneman, 1991). We can speculate that religions may encourage forms of voluntary "loss" in their adherents to exploit this fallacy.}
