One might object that practices like extreme fasting or celibacy are not actually common in popular religion, and are only seen in small, devout groups like Monks. Obviously, celibacy could not become a dominant meme as it would lead to human extinction; those not buying into it would naturally outcompete those who do. However, it is still a valuable example for two reasons. Firstly, it demonstrates how a mind virus can infect a not unreasonable number of people; i.e., while celibacy is not a predominant meme, it is still a surviving meme and it has been passed on despite it being clearly maladaptive. Secondly, most religions still have some form of sexual restriction (i.e. monogamy in the Abrahamic triad)\u8212\'97despite many partners being good for genetic diversity\u8212\'97in which the general principle of sacrificial sunk costs may apply (Balzarini et al., 2019).}
